# Google API Configuration for TimeBeacon Integration
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual values

# ===========================================
# GOOGLE CLOUD CONSOLE CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================
# Get these values from: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials

# Google OAuth 2.0 Client ID (ends with .apps.googleusercontent.com)
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id_here.apps.googleusercontent.com

# Google OAuth 2.0 Client Secret (keep this secure!)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret_here

# OAuth 2.0 Redirect URI (must match exactly what's configured in Google Cloud Console)
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=https://app.timebeacon.io/auth/callback

# Google API Key (optional, for higher rate limits)
REACT_APP_GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# ===========================================
# REQUIRED GOOGLE APIS TO ENABLE
# ===========================================
# Enable these APIs in Google Cloud Console:
# 1. Google Drive API: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/drive.googleapis.com
# 2. Gmail API: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/gmail.googleapis.com  
# 3. Google Calendar API: https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/library/calendar.googleapis.com

# ===========================================
# OAUTH CONSENT SCREEN CONFIGURATION
# ===========================================
# In Google Cloud Console > APIs & Services > OAuth consent screen:
# - App name: TimeBeacon
# - User support email: your@email.com
# - Developer contact: your@email.com
# - App domain: https://app.timebeacon.io
# - Privacy Policy: https://timebeacon.io/privacy
# - Terms of Service: https://timebeacon.io/tos
# 
# Required Scopes:
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/gmail.readonly
# - https://www.googleapis.com/auth/calendar
#
# Authorized redirect URIs:
# - https://app.timebeacon.io/auth/callback
# - http://localhost:3000/auth/callback (for development)

# ===========================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ===========================================
# For production deployment, set these in your hosting platform:
# - Vercel: Project Settings > Environment Variables
# - Netlify: Site Settings > Environment Variables  
# - Render: Environment > Environment Variables
# - Heroku: Settings > Config Vars

# ===========================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ===========================================
# - Never commit .env.local or .env files with real values to version control
# - Keep your Client Secret secure and never expose it in frontend code
# - Use HTTPS in production for all redirect URIs
# - Regularly rotate your API keys and secrets
# - Monitor usage in Google Cloud Console quotas section